DIGEST
SB 375 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Mizell
Present law defines "testing" as calibration testing, conformance testing, or fixed system
testing.
Proposed law changes the definition to the evaluation of fire fighting equipment, systems,
or foam concentrates for operability, performance verification, calibration, conformance to
manufacturer specifications, or regulatory compliance including but not limited to discharge
testing of fixed fire suppression systems, mobile apparatus testing, proportioning system
calibrations, and system acceptance testing. Further provides "testing" does not include
emergency fire fighting operations.
Proposed law defines "training" as instruction, drills, exercises, demonstrations, or other
activities conducted to familiarize personnel with the deployment, handling, storage, mixing,
proportioning, or application of fire fighting foam, including live fire exercises and
simulated fire response scenarios. Further provides "training" does not include emergency
fire fighting operations.
Effective August 1, 2026.
(Amends R.S. 40:1615(A)(4); adds R.S. 40:1615(A)(5))
